4
00:00:53,136 --> 00:00:57,936
[Q. I Know This Is Hard,
But Can You Describe What Happened?

5
00:01:00,270 --> 00:01:03,281
It was just like any other day.

6
00:01:05,984 --> 00:01:10,454
My mom was yelling at me
to bring her more alcohol.

7
00:01:12,908 --> 00:01:17,461
She hit me a few times, so I got scared
and ran into the bathroom.

8
00:01:42,687 --> 00:01:44,439
Dad,

9
00:01:44,439 --> 00:01:47,651
Can't you stop her when she's hitting me?

10
00:01:47,651 --> 00:01:53,247
You just stand there and watch,
so she gets drunk and takes it out on me.

11
00:01:54,407 --> 00:01:55,575
Pathetic.

12
00:01:55,575 --> 00:01:59,121
[Q. Then Do You Remember
What Your Father Was Doing?

13
00:01:59,121 --> 00:02:00,664
Your mom...

14
00:02:00,664 --> 00:02:04,918
How am I supposed to stop her
when she's drunk and raising hell?

15
00:02:04,918 --> 00:02:08,804
She refuses to grant me a divorce
and just acts like a total psycho.

16
00:02:12,300 --> 00:02:14,185
It hurts.

17
00:02:14,845 --> 00:02:18,849
At first, he tried to stop her.

18
00:02:18,849 --> 00:02:22,109
But eventually, I think
he just went to sleep.

19
00:02:42,372 --> 00:02:45,216
So long, wife.

20
00:03:06,772 --> 00:03:09,073
You didn't throw her, did you?

21
00:03:12,861 --> 00:03:16,323
Your mother was drunk
and fell down the stairs.

22
00:03:16,323 --> 00:03:19,159
Be honest. You were sick of her too,
weren't you?

23
00:03:19,159 --> 00:03:23,080
I'll get you a new mom.

24
00:03:23,080 --> 00:03:25,874
And she's loaded.

25
00:03:25,874 --> 00:03:28,759
It's nothing compared to this dump.

26
00:03:29,419 --> 00:03:32,972
From now on, you do exactly as I say.

27
00:03:34,007 --> 00:03:37,685
Or else I'll throw you down there too.

28
00:04:47,581 --> 00:04:49,875
Ah Jin.

29
00:04:49,875 --> 00:04:53,177
Please... call 911.

30
00:05:37,631 --> 00:05:40,975
[Name: Baek Ah Jin, Actress]

31
00:05:57,859 --> 00:06:01,613
[Has Antisocial Personality Disorder
Which Affects 4% Of The Population]

32
00:06:01,613 --> 00:06:04,582
[She Is A Sociopath]

33
00:06:13,375 --> 00:06:19,096
[She Views Others As Tools To Be
Manipulated For Her Own Personal Gain]

34
00:06:20,048 --> 00:06:27,855
[She Deliberately Targeted Men
Who Could Be of Use To Her]

35
00:06:38,774 --> 00:06:40,318
[While She Has Never Directly Committed Murder,]

36
00:06:40,318 --> 00:06:45,081
[She's Responsible For The Deaths
Of Two People - Baek, Heo]

37
00:06:51,663 --> 00:06:56,999
[She Has A Murder Plot
That Has Yet To Be Carried Out]

38
00:07:09,973 --> 00:07:13,852
[She Is The Actress, Baek Ah Jin]

39
00:07:13,852 --> 00:07:18,940
[Episode 1: Her X's]

40
00:07:18,940 --> 00:07:20,525
[July 2016]

41
00:07:20,525 --> 00:07:22,736
The homeroom teacher's having a party.
Let's go watch!

42
00:07:22,736 --> 00:07:24,821
What are you waiting for? Let's go!

43
00:07:24,821 --> 00:07:26,198
- Hey, let's go get some cake.
- Cake?

44
00:07:26,198 --> 00:07:27,991
- Hey, come on, let's go!
- Yeah, hurry up!

45
00:07:27,991 --> 00:07:29,826
- Bring some for me!
- Me too!

46
00:07:29,826 --> 00:07:31,711
Me too!

47
00:07:42,923 --> 00:07:45,182
I got it right up to here, right?

48
00:07:46,718 --> 00:07:49,596
- ♪ Happy birthday to you ♪
- ♪ Happy birthday to you ♪

49
00:07:49,596 --> 00:07:52,057
- ♪ Happy birthday to you ♪
- ♪ Happy birthday to you ♪

50
00:07:52,057 --> 00:07:55,685
- ♪ Happy birthday, dear teacher... ♪
- ♪ Happy birthday, dear teacher... ♪

51
00:07:55,685 --> 00:07:57,395
- Singwang High.
- Yes, this is Singwang High.

52
00:07:57,395 --> 00:07:59,614
The poster was anonymous, so...

53
00:08:09,783 --> 00:08:11,542
What the hell is this?

54
00:08:12,119 --> 00:08:14,003
I said, what is this?

55
00:08:22,379 --> 00:08:24,297
- Is this for real?
- Who is that?

56
00:08:24,297 --> 00:08:28,343
- It's our homeroom teacher.
- What kind of behavior is this?

57
00:08:28,343 --> 00:08:31,638
It's all over the school's website.

58
00:08:31,638 --> 00:08:35,058
We're being flooded with complaint calls
from parents. It's a total mess.

59
00:08:35,058 --> 00:08:38,061
So, just lie low until things die down,

60
00:08:38,061 --> 00:08:40,605
and we'll contact you
once we've sorted things out.

61
00:08:40,605 --> 00:08:43,115
[Principal's Office]

62
00:08:57,372 --> 00:09:00,216
Are you okay, Ms. Kwak?

63
00:09:04,838 --> 00:09:07,515
Did you like my gift?

64
00:09:08,759 --> 00:09:11,094
Just like you always taught us,

65
00:09:11,094 --> 00:09:14,514
I'm just a poor girl with no guardians,
let alone parents,

66
00:09:14,514 --> 00:09:17,309
so I couldn't get you
anything extravagant.

67
00:09:17,309 --> 00:09:21,404
But I did prepare it with all my heart,
in my own way.

68
00:09:22,147 --> 00:09:24,907
I really hope you liked it.

69
00:09:26,777 --> 00:09:28,953
Happy birthday.

70
00:09:37,329 --> 00:09:40,064
[Sim Sung Hee: Her X]

71
00:09:47,672 --> 00:09:52,177
Ah Jin and I both got one question wrong,
so why am I ranked second?

72
00:09:52,177 --> 00:09:56,264
The art test had a one-point difference.
Your ranks are different,

73
00:09:56,264 --> 00:09:59,351
but you both got the top grade,
so it's not a big deal.

74
00:09:59,351 --> 00:10:01,235
The art practical?

75
00:10:03,020 --> 00:10:07,734
[One Month Earlier]

76
00:10:07,734 --> 00:10:09,660
What's that?

77
00:10:10,278 --> 00:10:12,781
That's Baek Ah Jin...
and who is that with her?

78
00:10:12,781 --> 00:10:14,749
The art teacher?

79
00:10:18,537 --> 00:10:20,580
You're still here?

80
00:10:20,580 --> 00:10:23,041
I left my umbrella in the classroom.

81
00:10:23,041 --> 00:10:25,085
I don't think there was
anything left in there.

82
00:10:25,085 --> 00:10:27,170
Then are you saying
someone took my umbrella?

83
00:10:27,170 --> 00:10:29,047
Yes.

84
00:10:29,047 --> 00:10:31,716
Move. I'll go look for myself.

85
00:10:31,716 --> 00:10:35,144
Come on.
I'll walk you home before it gets late.

86
00:10:36,012 --> 00:10:37,647
Okay.

87
00:10:43,520 --> 00:10:45,313
Leave it to the model student.

88
00:10:45,313 --> 00:10:48,150
Studying even with all this noise.

89
00:10:48,150 --> 00:10:50,694
So, who were you with in the classroom?

90
00:10:50,694 --> 00:10:53,871
It was the art teacher from study hall
last night, wasn't it?

91
00:10:56,032 --> 00:10:58,618
You're pretty nosy, aren't you?

92
00:10:58,618 --> 00:11:00,753
And pretty clueless, too.

93
00:11:02,873 --> 00:11:05,800
In the movies, the nosy ones
are always the first to die.

94
00:11:07,335 --> 00:11:09,463
But you're lucky.

95
00:11:09,463 --> 00:11:12,890
At least in the real world,
you don't get killed for being nosy.

96
00:11:19,097 --> 00:11:22,559
In that moment, a chill ran down my spine.

97
00:11:22,559 --> 00:11:25,145
That look on Baek Ah Jin's face...

98
00:11:25,145 --> 00:11:27,022
her tone...

99
00:11:27,022 --> 00:11:30,324
her true colors, which vanished in a flash.

100
00:11:31,526 --> 00:11:34,571
And I was the only one who saw it.

101
00:11:34,571 --> 00:11:39,451
Congrats to Ah Jin, our top student,
and Joon Seo, who won the writing contest.

102
00:11:39,451 --> 00:11:43,997
Joon Seo and Sung Hee, for the debate,
you two need to step it up.

103
00:11:43,997 --> 00:11:47,417
I'd like to give my place
in the debate to Baek Ah Jin.

104
00:11:47,417 --> 00:11:49,167
All of a sudden?

105
00:11:49,167 --> 00:11:50,212
Why?

106
00:11:50,212 --> 00:11:54,424
I can use my award for early admission
as a Student with Literary Talent.

107
00:11:54,424 --> 00:11:56,676
Really?
Have you spoken to Ah Jin about this?

108
00:11:56,676 --> 00:11:59,471
Yes. I'd really like to participate if I can.

109
00:11:59,471 --> 00:12:03,183
All right, I'll check your eligibility
and let you know.

110
00:12:03,183 --> 00:12:04,976
Good luck with your next classes!

111
00:12:04,976 --> 00:12:07,028
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

112
00:12:10,440 --> 00:12:12,946
[2016 President's Cup Debate Participants]
[Sim Sung Hee, Yoon Joon Seo...]

113
00:12:14,444 --> 00:12:17,823
Okay, the topic for the debate is
the pros and cons of the death penalty.

114
00:12:17,823 --> 00:12:22,369
Part 1 is an open presentation.
For Part 2, one person will represent us

115
00:12:22,369 --> 00:12:26,873
to argue for or against it with others.
You guys only need to prepare for Part 1.

116
00:12:26,873 --> 00:12:30,710
Yu Bin, you and Ah Jin
can do the research.

117
00:12:30,710 --> 00:12:32,629
And Ga Yeong,
you prepare the presentation.

118
00:12:32,629 --> 00:12:34,297
I'll write the script.

119
00:12:34,297 --> 00:12:36,925
It's just easier
if the presenter writes it.

120
00:12:36,925 --> 00:12:38,768
- Okay.
- Sounds good.

121
00:12:41,346 --> 00:12:44,273
Is this how you always make decisions?

122
00:12:45,016 --> 00:12:47,477
Ah Jin, we're all okay with it.

123
00:12:47,477 --> 00:12:49,771
This is how we did
the Idea Pitching Competition, too.

124
00:12:49,771 --> 00:12:53,150
Sung Hee's a great leader,
so we have a better chance of winning.

125
00:12:53,150 --> 00:12:55,485
No, it's okay, guys.

126
00:12:55,485 --> 00:12:58,113
I guess I was being too presumptuous.

127
00:12:58,113 --> 00:12:59,781
Ah Jin,

128
00:12:59,781 --> 00:13:02,291
then how would you like to do it?

129
00:13:03,034 --> 00:13:06,788
I heard that teamwork is a big part
of the score.

130
00:13:06,788 --> 00:13:09,082
In that case, to get a good score,

131
00:13:09,082 --> 00:13:12,176
wouldn't it be better if we also split Part 2?

132
00:13:14,880 --> 00:13:17,090
Ah Jin has a point.

133
00:13:17,090 --> 00:13:20,594
All right, then let's each think about
how to split the work,

134
00:13:20,594 --> 00:13:23,346
and decide next time we meet. How's that?

135
00:13:23,346 --> 00:13:25,147
Sure.

136
00:13:31,772 --> 00:13:33,148
- Goodbye.
- Bye.

137
00:13:33,148 --> 00:13:34,483
- See you guys later.
- Bye!

138
00:13:34,483 --> 00:13:36,276
Bye.

139
00:13:36,276 --> 00:13:39,112
- Good job today.
- Damn it, I'm so pissed.

140
00:13:39,112 --> 00:13:41,656
Are you on your period? Why the hysterics?

141
00:13:41,656 --> 00:13:46,627
She waltzes in, preaching about teamwork.
That crazy bitch.

142
00:13:48,121 --> 00:13:52,000
Baek Ah Jin? The one who
knocked you out of first place?

143
00:13:52,000 --> 00:13:53,710
Mom.

144
00:13:53,710 --> 00:13:56,546
Don't worry. I'll take care of it.

145
00:13:56,546 --> 00:14:00,300
As the parent rep, do you know how much
I donate to your school every month?

146
00:14:00,300 --> 00:14:02,351
You think I can't handle this?

147
00:14:03,637 --> 00:14:08,183
Can you find out what private tutoring
Baek Ah Jin is getting?

148
00:14:08,183 --> 00:14:09,726
What are you talking about?

149
00:14:09,726 --> 00:14:12,729
Teacher Kwak told me she's an orphan.
She can't even afford extra lessons.

150
00:14:12,729 --> 00:14:16,233
Speaking of which, we spent
so much money on that woman.

151
00:14:16,233 --> 00:14:19,986
Now that she's fired, the money's wasted.
And it wasn't just money, either.

152
00:14:19,986 --> 00:14:22,948
She said she needed legal advice,
so your dad even helped her out.

153
00:14:22,948 --> 00:14:26,292
Who on earth did she get caught
having an affair with?

154
00:15:48,408 --> 00:15:49,910
Are you feeling sick?

155
00:15:49,910 --> 00:15:52,086
I think you have a fever.

156
00:15:53,663 --> 00:15:55,957
No, I'm fine.

157
00:15:55,957 --> 00:15:57,758
Just get back to it.

158
00:16:01,046 --> 00:16:03,298
It's after 11. You should go home.

159
00:16:03,298 --> 00:16:06,183
I'm more comfortable here than at home.

160
00:16:07,636 --> 00:16:09,763
Hey, can I borrow your literature notes?

161
00:16:09,763 --> 00:16:11,689
Sure, one second.

162
00:16:14,810 --> 00:16:16,611
Here you go.

163
00:16:27,739 --> 00:16:31,451
Joon Seo, about you dropping out
of the Debate Competition...

164
00:16:31,451 --> 00:16:33,995
Did Baek Ah Jin ask you to do it, by any chance?

165
00:16:33,995 --> 00:16:36,748
No, it just doesn't feel like
the right fit for me.

166
00:16:36,748 --> 00:16:38,667
But we're president and vice president.

167
00:16:38,667 --> 00:16:40,794
It would look good if we competed together.

168
00:16:40,794 --> 00:16:45,215
Having Ah Jin take my place
will give us a better chance of winning.

169
00:16:45,215 --> 00:16:50,303
No, Joon Seo, you're such a good writer.
You competing would be much more helpful.

170
00:16:50,303 --> 00:16:52,514
Can't you just say you'll do it?

171
00:16:52,514 --> 00:16:54,690
Let's talk about this later.

172
00:16:59,729 --> 00:17:02,190
Did Sim Sung Hee give you this?

173
00:17:02,190 --> 00:17:04,025
[Dear Joon Seo. Hi, it's Sung Hee.]

174
00:17:04,025 --> 00:17:06,118
Did that come out of my bag?

175
00:17:07,028 --> 00:17:08,530
I had absolutely no idea.

176
00:17:08,530 --> 00:17:09,779
[You've probably noticed, but I like you...]

177
00:17:09,779 --> 00:17:11,939
[I heard you're single,
so what do you think about me?]

178
00:17:12,659 --> 00:17:15,579
Why the serious face? Just throw it out.

179
00:17:15,579 --> 00:17:17,956
[Please think about it and text me back.
[I'll be waiting! Bye.]

180
00:17:17,956 --> 00:17:20,716
You should at least write back to her.

181
00:17:22,377 --> 00:17:24,220
I'll do it for you.

182
00:17:32,012 --> 00:17:33,847
Hey, did you hear the rumor this morning?

183
00:17:33,847 --> 00:17:37,108
- Yeah, about Baek Ah Jin?
- That she doesn't have a mom.

184
00:17:39,644 --> 00:17:41,813
That rumor from earlier was about
Baek Ah Jin, right?

185
00:17:41,813 --> 00:17:43,231
Yeah, it was.

186
00:17:43,231 --> 00:17:45,324
Ah Jin.

187
00:17:47,194 --> 00:17:50,030
Yesterday, Sung Hee was telling Yu Bin

188
00:17:50,030 --> 00:17:53,492
that you live by yourself without any parents.

189
00:17:53,492 --> 00:17:55,994
And she knows Yu Bin has a big mouth,

190
00:17:55,994 --> 00:17:59,331
so by now, everyone in our class
and the whole sophomore year knows.

191
00:17:59,331 --> 00:18:01,132
What are you going to do?

192
00:18:02,626 --> 00:18:04,377
About the Debate Competition.

193
00:18:04,377 --> 00:18:06,880
There's not much time left,

194
00:18:06,880 --> 00:18:11,968
We've had complaints from parents that
a new member would disrupt the team.

195
00:18:11,968 --> 00:18:16,723
So the principal has decided to stick with
the three original members.

196
00:18:16,723 --> 00:18:20,811
Which parent is it that's objecting
to me joining the team?

197
00:18:20,811 --> 00:18:22,896
This is my dad.
You've seen him on TV, right?

198
00:18:22,896 --> 00:18:24,731
- Yeah, I have.
- See?

199
00:18:24,731 --> 00:18:25,941
Yeah, totally.

200
00:18:25,941 --> 00:18:28,151
And this is my mom.

201
00:18:28,151 --> 00:18:32,656
- Wow, she's gorgeous.
- You look just like her.

202
00:18:32,656 --> 00:18:34,366
- I'm so jealous, Sung Hee.
- Wow, great photo.

203
00:18:34,366 --> 00:18:36,076
- Wow, her family's loaded.
- Really? Is it a good picture?

204
00:18:36,076 --> 00:18:39,128
- I'm seriously so jealous.
- I know, right?

205
00:18:47,546 --> 00:18:49,005
But...

206
00:18:49,005 --> 00:18:51,641
Is it true you don't have parents?

207
00:18:56,304 --> 00:18:58,512
Ah Jin!

208
00:18:58,512 --> 00:18:59,584
Ah Jin!

209
00:18:59,584 --> 00:19:01,609
I'm so sorry.

210
00:19:07,357 --> 00:19:11,611
I heard you got removed from the debate club.

211
00:19:11,611 --> 00:19:15,240
I guess Ga Yeong's
and Yu Bin's moms complained.

212
00:19:15,240 --> 00:19:17,583
Do you like Yoon Joon Seo?

213
00:19:22,456 --> 00:19:25,007
Did Joon Seo tell you?

214
00:19:28,712 --> 00:19:30,756
Joon Seo asked me to give this to you.

215
00:19:30,756 --> 00:19:33,015
I think he felt sorry to give it to you himself.

216
00:19:39,261 --> 00:19:40,390
[Nobody likes you]

217
00:19:40,390 --> 00:19:42,184
[You're An Annoying Try-hard]

218
00:19:42,184 --> 00:19:43,315
[Stop This Attention Seeking]

219
00:19:46,855 --> 00:19:48,315
Sung Hee.

220
00:19:48,315 --> 00:19:50,400
The homeroom teacher is looking for you.

221
00:19:50,400 --> 00:19:52,402
We've been notified by the debate organizers

222
00:19:52,402 --> 00:19:54,905
that our school's been disqualified.

223
00:19:54,905 --> 00:20:00,118
Apparently, someone tipped them off,
and the organizers don't want controversy.

224
00:20:00,118 --> 00:20:03,045
I'm afraid we'll have to pull out
of this competition.

225
00:20:06,958 --> 00:20:08,600
[President's Cup Debate Competition]

226
00:20:10,087 --> 00:20:11,713
[Debate Competition Contestant Bribes Judge]

227
00:20:11,713 --> 00:20:13,090
[A Singwang High Contestant's Parent]

228
00:20:13,090 --> 00:20:14,591
[Approached A Judge To Secure An Award]

229
00:20:14,591 --> 00:20:15,717
[And Allegedly Offered A Bribe]

230
00:20:15,717 --> 00:20:16,968
[Requesting A Fact-Check On This]

231
00:20:16,968 --> 00:20:18,053
[They've Also Been Replacing]

232
00:20:18,053 --> 00:20:19,137
[And Unjustly Removing Members]

233
00:20:19,137 --> 00:20:20,980
[I Demand The Organizers Act]

234
00:20:26,186 --> 00:20:28,480
Considering the circumstances,
it had to be her!

235
00:20:28,480 --> 00:20:32,692
Since she couldn't go,
she spread a rumor so none of us could go.

236
00:20:32,692 --> 00:20:34,493
Damn it.

237
00:20:35,112 --> 00:20:36,947
Don't worry, Mom.

238
00:20:36,947 --> 00:20:38,740
You know me.

239
00:20:38,740 --> 00:20:43,002
Of all the bitches who've messed with me,
not a single one has gotten away clean.

240
00:20:43,995 --> 00:20:47,548
I'm curious what happens to the bitches
who mess with you.

241
00:20:50,001 --> 00:20:52,553
You spread the rumor, didn't you?
That I'm an orphan.

242
00:20:53,213 --> 00:20:54,798
Thanks a lot.

243
00:20:54,798 --> 00:20:57,175
Thanks to you, school life's
about to get real interesting.

244
00:20:57,175 --> 00:21:01,304
Don't welfare recipients
get free rice from the government?

245
00:21:01,304 --> 00:21:03,723
And your tuition is free, too.

246
00:21:03,723 --> 00:21:06,017
That rice you eat...

247
00:21:06,017 --> 00:21:08,653
is paid for by my dad's taxes.

248
00:21:10,605 --> 00:21:12,531
Thanks.

249
00:21:32,043 --> 00:21:33,295
[Nobody likes you]

250
00:21:33,295 --> 00:21:35,046
[Expressing Futility, Negative...]

251
00:21:35,046 --> 00:21:36,965
You're an annoying...

252
00:21:36,965 --> 00:21:38,006
[Expressing...]

253
00:21:38,006 --> 00:21:39,049
Annoying...

254
00:21:39,049 --> 00:21:42,763
Fuck, the handwriting's exactly the same.

255
00:21:42,763 --> 00:21:44,097
Fuck.

256
00:21:44,097 --> 00:21:45,474
[You checking the books?]

257
00:21:45,474 --> 00:21:46,641
[Studying for a test]

258
00:21:46,641 --> 00:21:48,351
[Okay]

259
00:21:48,351 --> 00:21:50,312
[Where are you?]

260
00:21:50,312 --> 00:21:54,115
Kim Byeong Jin from Class 5.
He's dodging the collection. What do I do?

261
00:22:00,822 --> 00:22:02,748
Stick to the protocol.

262
00:22:10,999 --> 00:22:15,098
[Dowonjang Chinese Restaurant]

263
00:22:36,858 --> 00:22:38,659
Hey.

264
00:22:40,028 --> 00:22:43,115
Don't get it twisted
and think you're someone special.

265
00:22:43,115 --> 00:22:44,783
Okay?

266
00:22:44,783 --> 00:22:47,460
Piss me off, and you'll be the only one
who regrets it.

267
00:22:48,203 --> 00:22:50,247
Got it?

268
00:22:50,247 --> 00:22:52,340
A nobody like you.

269
00:23:06,513 --> 00:23:09,683
So you go to the same school as my Byeong Jin?

270
00:23:09,683 --> 00:23:11,560
Yeah, Byeong Jin and I are practically...

271
00:23:11,560 --> 00:23:13,979
like brothers.

272
00:23:13,979 --> 00:23:16,155
Close enough to lend him...

273
00:23:17,566 --> 00:23:19,609
even 250,000 won of my hard-earned money.

274
00:23:19,609 --> 00:23:21,236
What are you talking about?

275
00:23:21,236 --> 00:23:24,489
Byeong Jin borrowed money?

276
00:23:24,489 --> 00:23:26,908
Don't believe me? Take a look.

277
00:23:26,908 --> 00:23:28,960
The loan agreement.

278
00:23:31,913 --> 00:23:34,833
He said a friend broke his headset, or whatever.

279
00:23:34,833 --> 00:23:37,544
Anyway, with interest, it's 300,000 won total.

280
00:23:37,544 --> 00:23:40,255
He was supposed to pay me back
5,000 won a day,

281
00:23:40,255 --> 00:23:43,300
but that little punk Byeong Jin
paid me for ten days and then bailed.

282
00:23:43,300 --> 00:23:46,352
You're a student. Focus on your studies.
How could you do this?

283
00:23:49,973 --> 00:23:51,641
Listen, lady.

284
00:23:51,641 --> 00:23:54,652
Are you going to pay me back or not?

285
00:23:55,187 --> 00:23:57,314
Just answer me that.

286
00:23:57,314 --> 00:24:00,317
Now, to discuss the meaning
of the Theory of Innate Goodness,

287
00:24:00,317 --> 00:24:03,403
- There are four virtues...
- Joon Seo.

288
00:24:03,403 --> 00:24:07,783
- Forget the money and just get rid of him.
- Please!

289
00:24:07,783 --> 00:24:10,869
Which are Righteousness, Propriety, and Wisdom.

290
00:24:10,869 --> 00:24:15,999
The concept is these virtues are inherent
in our nature as a complete moral system.

291
00:24:15,999 --> 00:24:21,213
It's a mistake to interpret the Theory of
Innate Evil as "human nature is evil."

292
00:24:21,213 --> 00:24:23,924
That since we're inherently evil,
we should just be evil our whole lives.

293
00:24:23,924 --> 00:24:26,968
That is absolutely not the case.
The philosopher who proposed

294
00:24:26,968 --> 00:24:29,437
the Theory of Innate Evil was
the great thinker, Xunzi.

295
00:24:32,808 --> 00:24:35,192
Sorry I'm late.

296
00:24:46,530 --> 00:24:49,332
I'm taking Ah Jin to the nurse's office.

297
00:24:51,118 --> 00:24:54,496
- Whoa, are they dating?
- What was that about?

298
00:24:54,496 --> 00:24:56,172
Quiet.

299
00:24:57,040 --> 00:24:59,050
Fucking hell.

300
00:25:00,419 --> 00:25:02,504
This weather is fucking crazy.

301
00:25:02,504 --> 00:25:05,549
How many raindrops can fall in a single second?

302
00:25:05,549 --> 00:25:09,094
Damn it, I just washed my uniform yesterday.

303
00:25:09,094 --> 00:25:10,804
What the hell?

304
00:25:10,804 --> 00:25:13,348
Don't tell me you two are ditching.

305
00:25:13,348 --> 00:25:16,400
And what happened to you?
Did you take a shower or something?

306
00:25:16,893 --> 00:25:18,520
I was in the rain,
but you're the one who's soaked.

307
00:25:18,520 --> 00:25:22,114
I thought I told you not to act
like you know me at school.

308
00:25:22,816 --> 00:25:24,818
Since you're here, just go to class quietly.

309
00:25:24,818 --> 00:25:27,320
Who the fuck are you to tell me
what to do, you bastard?

310
00:25:27,320 --> 00:25:29,614
And who's the one ditching class right now, huh?

311
00:25:29,614 --> 00:25:32,124
We're not ditching.
We're going to the nurse's office.

312
00:25:32,784 --> 00:25:34,161
Also, those AirPods...

313
00:25:34,161 --> 00:25:36,754
You're not supposed to
let anyone see those, right?

314
00:25:39,666 --> 00:25:41,877
[One Month Earlier]

315
00:25:41,877 --> 00:25:43,844
Aren't these expensive?

316
00:25:50,177 --> 00:25:52,220
For real? You're not going to snitch?

317
00:25:52,220 --> 00:25:55,807
- Why not?
- I don't meddle in others' business.

318
00:25:55,807 --> 00:25:59,485
I guess a model student like you
has nothing to gain by getting involved.

319
00:26:00,270 --> 00:26:05,366
Is there anything you need?
Want something? I can swipe it for you.

320
00:26:06,151 --> 00:26:07,819
I don't need any stuff,

321
00:26:07,819 --> 00:26:09,696
but I do need a person.

322
00:26:09,696 --> 00:26:10,736
A person?

323
00:26:10,736 --> 00:26:14,701
It's a job that's perfect for you.
And it pays, so this works out.

324
00:26:14,701 --> 00:26:16,161
[Bong Soo Hoon - 10,000 Won/Day For 7 Days]

325
00:26:16,161 --> 00:26:18,087
[Late Fee: 10 Percent Per Day]

326
00:26:19,247 --> 00:26:20,582
[Boss]

327
00:26:20,582 --> 00:26:22,834
I'll be in the nurse's office,
then I'm leaving for the day.

328
00:26:22,834 --> 00:26:25,052
I'll check the books tomorrow.

329
00:26:27,380 --> 00:26:31,551
Well, look at you. Lost in thought?
What's this?

330
00:26:31,551 --> 00:26:33,720
"Touch and you die."
Kim Jae Oh, what is this?

331
00:26:33,720 --> 00:26:36,731
You little... you startled me.
Hey! Get back here!

332
00:26:37,516 --> 00:26:40,192
Hey! Somebody grab him!

333
00:26:40,769 --> 00:26:42,145
What? What's going on?

334
00:26:42,145 --> 00:26:44,113
You're dead meat when I catch you!

335
00:26:45,690 --> 00:26:47,491
What was that?

336
00:26:48,318 --> 00:26:50,995
- What just happened?
- What was that?

337
00:26:58,161 --> 00:27:00,046
What's this?

338
00:27:06,086 --> 00:27:07,212
Collecting money? Why would he...

339
00:27:07,212 --> 00:27:08,505
[I'll Check The Books Tomorrow!]

340
00:27:08,505 --> 00:27:10,132
The books... Boss?

341
00:27:10,132 --> 00:27:11,891
[Stick To The Protocol]

342
00:27:12,926 --> 00:27:15,679
- What is all this?
- Sim Sung Hee?

343
00:27:15,679 --> 00:27:18,056
Why would she do something like that to you?

344
00:27:18,056 --> 00:27:20,016
Why do you think?

345
00:27:20,016 --> 00:27:23,152
It's because she doesn't like me
hanging around with you.

346
00:27:25,939 --> 00:27:29,359
Whatever her reason, this is too far.
We should tell our homeroom teacher.

347
00:27:29,359 --> 00:27:31,653
Forget it. We're not kids.

348
00:27:31,653 --> 00:27:34,906
She was already on my nerves
for spreading weird rumors anyway.

349
00:27:34,906 --> 00:27:37,250
I'll take care of her my way.

350
00:27:38,743 --> 00:27:40,746
You should probably lie down for now.

351
00:27:40,746 --> 00:27:43,089
Besides, your hair is still wet.

352
00:27:43,623 --> 00:27:45,716
You're going to catch a cold.

353
00:27:48,128 --> 00:27:50,054
Joon Seo.

354
00:27:50,839 --> 00:27:53,015
Honestly, I'm scared.

355
00:27:54,676 --> 00:27:56,978
I'm scared of what she'll do next.

356
00:27:59,055 --> 00:28:01,148
You'll help me, right?

357
00:28:22,454 --> 00:28:25,290
- Hey, there's Ah Jin.
- Baek Ah Jin!

358
00:28:25,290 --> 00:28:27,751
Baek Ah Jin! Good morning!

359
00:28:27,751 --> 00:28:29,086
Hey, are you okay?

360
00:28:29,086 --> 00:28:32,214
Yeah, I'm totally fine. Thanks.

361
00:28:32,214 --> 00:28:35,675
Hey. You left early, so you missed it?

362
00:28:35,675 --> 00:28:39,137
So get this, Kim Jae Oh has been
loan-sharking to other students,

363
00:28:39,137 --> 00:28:41,723
and the ethics teacher totally caught him
with his ledger yesterday.

364
00:28:41,723 --> 00:28:43,558
I hear the amount was insane.

365
00:28:43,558 --> 00:28:46,019
You could hear our teacher yelling
from the hall yesterday.

366
00:28:46,019 --> 00:28:47,813
Totally.

367
00:28:47,813 --> 00:28:49,614
Really?

368
00:29:07,582 --> 00:29:09,383
You're here.

369
00:29:13,046 --> 00:29:16,849
I was gonna give you five more minutes,
and then I was out of here.

370
00:29:23,890 --> 00:29:26,025
You've heard, right?

371
00:29:27,936 --> 00:29:29,563
Hey, for what it's worth,

372
00:29:29,563 --> 00:29:32,274
I didn't say a single word
about you, okay?

373
00:29:32,274 --> 00:29:34,867
So I guess that makes us even-

374
00:29:46,496 --> 00:29:48,381
Thank you.

375
00:29:49,249 --> 00:29:52,718
I knew you'd do that for me.

376
00:30:02,471 --> 00:30:05,815
Hang on. My ribs.

377
00:30:10,520 --> 00:30:12,530
Did you get hit again?

378
00:30:21,198 --> 00:30:23,992
I really don't get it.

379
00:30:23,992 --> 00:30:29,046
Every time your father beats you,
I get so mad at how you act like an idiot.

380
00:30:30,665 --> 00:30:33,050
Don't you ever get sick of it?

381
00:30:34,544 --> 00:30:38,381
If it were me, I would've done
whatever it took to get out of there.

382
00:30:38,381 --> 00:30:40,383
Instead of just sitting there
and taking it like an idiot.

383
00:30:40,383 --> 00:30:43,553
I had no idea you were
so concerned about me.

384
00:30:43,553 --> 00:30:45,222
No wonder.

385
00:30:45,222 --> 00:30:48,100
The way you've been looking
at me felt so different.

386
00:30:48,100 --> 00:30:50,644
You thought I was pathetic,

387
00:30:50,644 --> 00:30:52,486
is that it?

388
00:30:54,523 --> 00:30:57,692
I just let him hit me.

389
00:30:57,692 --> 00:31:00,494
If he doesn't take it out on me,
he'll bother someone else.

390
00:31:01,279 --> 00:31:02,906
Besides,

391
00:31:02,906 --> 00:31:06,576
no matter how useless I am,
a son can't just beat his father, can he?

392
00:31:06,576 --> 00:31:08,753
No. You can.

393
00:31:10,038 --> 00:31:12,798
What's so wrong with putting yourself first?

394
00:31:16,002 --> 00:31:17,803
Kim Jae Oh.

395
00:31:18,755 --> 00:31:21,299
You're not useless.

396
00:31:21,299 --> 00:31:23,184
At least not to me.

397
00:31:59,463 --> 00:32:02,549
- They even have grilled beef patties.
- I was so hungry.

398
00:32:02,549 --> 00:32:04,718
Can I have one more?
I'm starving. I'll take broken pieces.

399
00:32:04,718 --> 00:32:05,886
That's plenty.

400
00:32:05,886 --> 00:32:08,472
Thank you!

401
00:32:08,472 --> 00:32:10,390
Hey, how'd you get four patties?

402
00:32:10,390 --> 00:32:12,184
What can I say? I'm her favorite.

403
00:32:12,184 --> 00:32:15,479
Right. Ah Jin, you're pitching in, right?
For our homeroom teacher's wedding gift.

404
00:32:15,479 --> 00:32:17,314
Yeah, of course I am.

405
00:32:17,314 --> 00:32:20,032
She's going to love it, right?

406
00:32:24,613 --> 00:32:26,865
No. You shouldn't.

407
00:32:26,865 --> 00:32:28,366
Hey, are you crazy?

408
00:32:28,366 --> 00:32:30,660
- What the hell?
- Sim Sung Hee! Ah Jin, are you okay?

409
00:32:30,660 --> 00:32:34,797
- Hey, you're soaked.
- It's okay. I'm just gonna go.

410
00:32:38,502 --> 00:32:40,845
- Hey, Baek Ah Jin!
- Ah Jin!

411
00:32:51,598 --> 00:32:54,233
So, you must be Kim Jae Oh's boss.

412
00:32:59,481 --> 00:33:01,365
You've been exposed...

413
00:33:02,943 --> 00:33:05,028
by me.

414
00:33:05,028 --> 00:33:06,446
So you really are the one in charge.

415
00:33:06,446 --> 00:33:10,499
The one pulling the strings,
making Kim Jae Oh collect money from kids.

416
00:33:11,034 --> 00:33:12,661
Playing the model student in public

417
00:33:12,661 --> 00:33:15,914
while secretly shaking down
kids for money.

418
00:33:15,914 --> 00:33:18,959
If the teacher finds out the gift was
bought with money you extorted,

419
00:33:18,959 --> 00:33:21,837
I'll bet she'd be just thrilled.

420
00:33:21,837 --> 00:33:23,679
Wouldn't she?

421
00:33:25,173 --> 00:33:26,925
Whatever will you do?

422
00:33:26,925 --> 00:33:29,936
You're not going to want to show
your face at school anymore.

423
00:33:33,849 --> 00:33:36,067
- Hey, get back here!
- Sung Hee.

424
00:33:37,727 --> 00:33:39,362
Can we talk for a second?

425
00:33:42,899 --> 00:33:44,909
So, why'd you pull me aside?

426
00:33:47,195 --> 00:33:50,323
It's about the reply to your note.
I'm sure you've figured it out,

427
00:33:50,323 --> 00:33:52,959
but Ah Jin was just messing around
when she wrote that.

428
00:33:54,286 --> 00:33:56,997
I'll apologize for her.

429
00:33:56,997 --> 00:33:59,124
I'm sorry.

430
00:33:59,124 --> 00:34:04,053
Forget it.
Tell Baek Ah Jin to apologize herself.

431
00:34:07,382 --> 00:34:09,426
I know you're mad, but...

432
00:34:09,426 --> 00:34:12,721
I don't want you to get the wrong idea.

433
00:34:12,721 --> 00:34:14,564
I like you.

434
00:34:16,433 --> 00:34:18,234
What?

435
00:34:19,352 --> 00:34:20,812
What did you just say?

436
00:34:20,812 --> 00:34:23,190
You said you like me, right?

437
00:34:23,190 --> 00:34:25,449
I'm saying I like you too.

438
00:34:28,987 --> 00:34:31,956
So, are we going out now?

439
00:34:37,245 --> 00:34:39,247
So, about that...

440
00:34:39,247 --> 00:34:43,710
You know, I really hate it
when people cross the line.

441
00:34:43,710 --> 00:34:47,881
I wouldn't want my girlfriend
to be that kind of person.

442
00:34:47,881 --> 00:34:49,549
What are you talking about?

443
00:34:49,549 --> 00:34:51,301
I've never done anything like that.

444
00:34:51,301 --> 00:34:54,971
It's just that there seems to be bad blood
between you and Baek Ah Jin lately.

445
00:34:54,971 --> 00:34:57,891
As you know, Baek Ah Jin and I go way back.

446
00:34:57,891 --> 00:35:01,269
If you really like me,
then while we're dating,

447
00:35:01,269 --> 00:35:04,155
I hope you'll leave Ah Jin alone.

448
00:35:04,815 --> 00:35:06,441
No, it's not like that.

449
00:35:06,441 --> 00:35:08,527
We're actually really close.

450
00:35:08,527 --> 00:35:11,530
Don't worry. I'm not like that.

451
00:35:11,530 --> 00:35:12,823
Really?

452
00:35:12,823 --> 00:35:15,951
- Yeah.
- Good. I'm glad to hear that.

453
00:35:15,951 --> 00:35:17,494
Any plans for the weekend?

454
00:35:17,494 --> 00:35:19,503
Wanna go see a movie?

455
00:35:21,039 --> 00:35:23,041
Sure, what should we see?

456
00:35:23,041 --> 00:35:25,252
Whatever you want to watch.

457
00:35:25,252 --> 00:35:27,546
What I want to watch?

458
00:35:27,546 --> 00:35:29,639
I'm good with anything.

459
00:35:31,883 --> 00:35:33,552
It's me.

460
00:35:33,552 --> 00:35:34,719
Who is this?

461
00:35:34,719 --> 00:35:37,222
Who do you think it is?
Did you forget my voice already?

462
00:35:37,222 --> 00:35:38,265
Kim Jae Oh?

463
00:35:38,265 --> 00:35:40,809
I got a second-hand phone.
Call this number from now on.

464
00:35:40,809 --> 00:35:42,936
That's all I called for. I'm hanging up.

465
00:35:42,936 --> 00:35:44,646
Wait.

466
00:35:44,646 --> 00:35:46,447
Don't hang up.

467
00:35:47,065 --> 00:35:49,283
I need you right now.

468
00:35:59,286 --> 00:36:03,790
You're always so quick with a comeback,
so why do you let others push you around?

469
00:36:03,790 --> 00:36:05,417
Sim Sung Hee...

470
00:36:05,417 --> 00:36:08,712
I think she found out everything
about the ledger.

471
00:36:08,712 --> 00:36:11,548
What do you mean, everything?
Even that you're the one behind it?

472
00:36:11,548 --> 00:36:13,425
She knows everything?

473
00:36:13,425 --> 00:36:17,144
Plus, she has that phone you lost.

474
00:36:18,180 --> 00:36:20,314
I'll go get it back from her right now.

475
00:36:21,933 --> 00:36:24,186
Don't do that.

476
00:36:24,186 --> 00:36:27,280
She already can't stand me as it is.

477
00:36:29,274 --> 00:36:32,451
It'll only be a matter of time
before it gets all over school.

478
00:36:33,028 --> 00:36:35,113
Everyone in school
will be talking about me.

479
00:36:35,113 --> 00:36:37,498
Shit.

480
00:36:43,163 --> 00:36:45,582
Does Yoon Joon Seo know what's going on?

481
00:36:45,582 --> 00:36:47,084
What's that bastard up to?

482
00:36:47,084 --> 00:36:49,176
You know how he is.

483
00:36:50,253 --> 00:36:52,672
Even if Joon Seo tried to step in,

484
00:36:52,672 --> 00:36:55,675
he can't handle someone like Sim Sung Hee
on his own.

485
00:36:55,675 --> 00:36:57,393
Right now, I just...

486
00:36:58,595 --> 00:37:01,105
I just need you to be there for me.

487
00:37:10,816 --> 00:37:12,317
Baek Ah Jin.

488
00:37:12,317 --> 00:37:14,201
Look at me.

489
00:37:15,904 --> 00:37:18,824
You know I learned to be perceptive
the hard way, right?

490
00:37:18,824 --> 00:37:22,244
Baek Ah Jin, you said it yourself.
That you need me.

491
00:37:22,244 --> 00:37:26,623
You're the smart one.
I bet you've already figured out a plan.

492
00:37:26,623 --> 00:37:28,424
So, tell me.

493
00:37:29,251 --> 00:37:31,302
What do you need me to do?

494
00:37:33,964 --> 00:37:37,141
Guys, hurry up and chip in
for the teacher's wedding gift.

495
00:37:41,096 --> 00:37:43,181
- What about you?
- Hey, Jung Hye Ji.

496
00:37:43,181 --> 00:37:44,099
Five thousand won.

497
00:37:44,099 --> 00:37:48,770
I heard Baek Ah Jin and Sim Sung Hee
had a big fight, pulling hair in the cafe.

498
00:37:48,770 --> 00:37:50,772
- Really? Why?
- Well, it wasn't exactly a fight.

499
00:37:50,772 --> 00:37:53,942
Sim Sung Hee snapped and poured
strawberry milk all over her tray.

500
00:37:53,942 --> 00:37:55,569
Strawberry milk? Is she crazy?

501
00:37:55,569 --> 00:37:57,411
Things are bad between them.

502
00:37:59,948 --> 00:38:01,283
I'll chip in now, too.

503
00:38:01,283 --> 00:38:04,157
Ah Jin. It's okay, you don't have to.

504
00:38:04,157 --> 00:38:05,245
Why not?

505
00:38:05,245 --> 00:38:08,331
Well, we've already collected quite a bit, so...

506
00:38:08,331 --> 00:38:10,709
Is it because of the rumor?
That I'm an orphan.

507
00:38:10,709 --> 00:38:12,794
No, that's not why.

508
00:38:12,794 --> 00:38:16,013
Do you know who started that rumor?

509
00:38:18,967 --> 00:38:20,927
Seriously?

510
00:38:20,927 --> 00:38:23,930
What's with that reaction?
Is something wrong?

511
00:38:23,930 --> 00:38:27,184
It's just... you two got together so suddenly.

512
00:38:27,184 --> 00:38:30,771
So Yoon Joon Seo asked you out
after you poured milk on Baek Ah Jin?

513
00:38:30,771 --> 00:38:34,065
I spilled it, I didn't pour it.

514
00:38:34,065 --> 00:38:36,242
Not a single drop even touched her face.

515
00:38:38,862 --> 00:38:40,238
Whatever.

516
00:38:40,238 --> 00:38:43,374
From now on, don't even bring up
Baek Ah Jin around me.

517
00:38:45,702 --> 00:38:47,670
I'm leaving.

518
00:38:51,666 --> 00:38:55,428
What's with her?
She loved trash-talking Baek Ah Jin.

519
00:38:57,631 --> 00:39:02,059
I like it, I like it

520
00:39:02,636 --> 00:39:04,645
How's it going with Joon Seo?

521
00:39:05,514 --> 00:39:07,849
You scared me.

522
00:39:07,849 --> 00:39:09,817
You two look good together.

523
00:39:12,020 --> 00:39:14,356
What's it to you?

524
00:39:14,356 --> 00:39:17,033
Treat him well. He's a good guy.

525
00:39:22,989 --> 00:39:24,449
[Boss]

526
00:39:24,449 --> 00:39:26,535
[Boss Pwd: 1004, Friday, 4th Period, P.E. Class]

527
00:39:26,535 --> 00:39:27,744
Angel? An angel?

528
00:39:27,744 --> 00:39:31,206
That crazy bitch, Sim Sung Hee.
That bitch has no shame.

529
00:39:31,206 --> 00:39:33,417
God, this is unbelievable.

530
00:39:33,417 --> 00:39:37,595
[Friday, 4th Period, P.E. Class]

531
00:39:51,435 --> 00:39:53,236
Joon Seo.

532
00:39:54,980 --> 00:39:57,315
I already bought our movie tickets
