533
00:39:57,315 --> 00:39:59,317
Thanks.

534
00:39:59,318 --> 00:40:10,318
Officail Website : kissasia.id  Translate by =Qari= @Team Viki

535
00:39:59,317 --> 00:40:03,196
Ugh, I hate P.E. so much.
It's hot and you get all sweaty.

536
00:40:03,196 --> 00:40:05,532
I wish this was a study hall instead.

537
00:40:05,532 --> 00:40:08,743
If you hate it that much,
you want to skip and hang out?

538
00:40:08,743 --> 00:40:12,372
We can just tell the teacher we're going
to the nurse's office, like Ah Jin did.

539
00:40:12,372 --> 00:40:14,750
Just sneak back to the classroom later.

540
00:40:14,750 --> 00:40:16,418
Don't tell the others.

541
00:40:16,418 --> 00:40:18,177
Okay!

542
00:40:26,428 --> 00:40:28,680
- Sir.
- Yes, Sung Hee? What's wrong?

543
00:40:28,680 --> 00:40:31,183
My stomach really hurts.

544
00:40:31,183 --> 00:40:33,018
And I feel nauseous.

545
00:40:33,018 --> 00:40:34,269
Is it that bad?

546
00:40:34,269 --> 00:40:37,647
I tried to push through it, but I just can't...

547
00:40:37,647 --> 00:40:40,734
I think I need to go to the nurse's office
for some medicine.

548
00:40:40,734 --> 00:40:44,453
- All right, go ahead. Can you go alone?
- Yes.

549
00:40:46,573 --> 00:40:49,993
Yes, Seon Hui and I will stop by
this weekend.

550
00:40:49,993 --> 00:40:51,286
Right, right.

551
00:40:51,286 --> 00:40:54,380
All right, take care, Father.

552
00:40:54,915 --> 00:40:57,675
You're always on the phone here.

553
00:41:00,420 --> 00:41:03,298
I was on my way to the nurse's office
and heard you talking.

554
00:41:03,298 --> 00:41:05,217
Are you not feeling well?

555
00:41:05,217 --> 00:41:06,885
I'm just not feeling too great.

556
00:41:06,885 --> 00:41:08,428
Is that right?

557
00:41:08,428 --> 00:41:10,138
Well, you should get going then.

558
00:41:10,138 --> 00:41:16,527
If you don't have a class,
could I talk to you for a second?

559
00:41:28,657 --> 00:41:31,250
[Come To The Art Room]
[Erase This!]

560
00:42:08,864 --> 00:42:11,958
[Sim Sung Hee]

561
00:42:17,539 --> 00:42:20,258
Sim Sung Hee just left the classroom.

562
00:42:22,586 --> 00:42:25,630
Ah Jin, what was it you wanted to say?

563
00:42:25,630 --> 00:42:29,009
I'm sorry. I'm just a little nervous.

564
00:42:29,009 --> 00:42:32,179
It's all right. Just relax and tell me
what's on your mind.

565
00:42:32,179 --> 00:42:33,972
Could...

566
00:42:33,972 --> 00:42:37,309
Could you hold my hand for a moment?

567
00:42:37,309 --> 00:42:39,186
Your hand?

568
00:42:39,186 --> 00:42:43,114
My hands start to shake whenever I get nervous.

569
00:42:59,998 --> 00:43:04,920
I know how much you've been looking out for me.

570
00:43:04,920 --> 00:43:07,054
And I've been giving it a lot of thought.

571
00:43:10,175 --> 00:43:14,729
About that "true love" you mentioned before.

572
00:43:17,933 --> 00:43:20,359
You've got to be kidding me.

573
00:43:21,770 --> 00:43:26,233
Well, back then... I just said that
out of genuine concern for you, Ah Jin-

574
00:43:26,233 --> 00:43:29,236
I understand how you feel now.

575
00:43:29,236 --> 00:43:31,704
What? "How you feel"?

576
00:43:34,324 --> 00:43:37,661
I pretended not to get it because
I was afraid my friends would find out,

577
00:43:37,661 --> 00:43:40,622
but I've regretted it ever since.

578
00:43:40,622 --> 00:43:44,126
It must have been so hard for you
to bring it up first.

579
00:43:44,126 --> 00:43:47,546
No, it's not like that. I just-

580
00:43:47,546 --> 00:43:50,514
I'll do whatever you want.

581
00:43:51,133 --> 00:43:53,893
I think I'm ready now.

582
00:44:07,941 --> 00:44:11,403
Thanks for your help.
It would've taken me forever by myself.

583
00:44:11,403 --> 00:44:15,782
Nah, don't worry about it.
Come on, the bell's gonna ring. Let's go.

584
00:44:15,782 --> 00:44:17,416
Yeah.

585
00:44:18,452 --> 00:44:21,580
Man... It'll probably be fine, right?

586
00:44:21,580 --> 00:44:22,748
What do you mean?

587
00:44:22,748 --> 00:44:24,916
Aren't we done with the supply check?

588
00:44:24,916 --> 00:44:28,837
Not that. I'm on classroom duty today.
I was about to lock up on my way out,

589
00:44:28,837 --> 00:44:31,798
but I couldn't find the lock,
so I just left it unlocked.

590
00:44:31,798 --> 00:44:34,384
You know our classroom's been broken into
a few times, right?

591
00:44:34,384 --> 00:44:36,303
So everyone in class is really sensitive about it.

592
00:44:36,303 --> 00:44:38,430
Then should you be announcing it like that?

593
00:44:38,430 --> 00:44:39,556
Huh?

594
00:44:39,556 --> 00:44:44,102
If the classroom actually gets robbed,
you'd be partly to blame, wouldn't you?

595
00:44:44,102 --> 00:44:47,189
If they don't find the thief and it gets
swept under the rug like last time,

596
00:44:47,189 --> 00:44:50,116
the other students might blame you.

597
00:44:51,943 --> 00:44:56,656
You never know, right?
It's better to be safe than sorry.

598
00:44:56,656 --> 00:44:58,200
It's so hot, I'm dying.

599
00:44:58,200 --> 00:45:01,328
- Changing out of gym clothes is a pain.
- Dude, you reek.

600
00:45:01,328 --> 00:45:03,038
Didn't Sim Sung Hee go
to the nurse's office?

601
00:45:03,038 --> 00:45:06,374
Hey, what happened to my desk?
Someone's gone through my stuff!

602
00:45:06,374 --> 00:45:09,427
- Hey, wasn't that...
- Where's the envelope?

603
00:45:11,751 --> 00:45:12,756
The envelope...

604
00:45:12,756 --> 00:45:15,634
- What's wrong?
- The envelope's gone.

605
00:45:15,634 --> 00:45:19,054
No way. Are you sure?
Maybe you put it elsewhere and forgot.

606
00:45:19,054 --> 00:45:22,182
I'm not mistaken.
I'm positive I put it in my notebook.

607
00:45:22,182 --> 00:45:26,485
That's where I always keep it.
I'm sure it was here right before P.E.

608
00:45:27,187 --> 00:45:28,647
Sim Sung Hee.

609
00:45:28,647 --> 00:45:30,690
Why were you in here by yourself?

610
00:45:30,690 --> 00:45:33,485
I wasn't feeling well,
so I was just resting in here.

611
00:45:33,485 --> 00:45:36,238
Then how'd you get in?

612
00:45:36,238 --> 00:45:37,864
It was already unlocked.

613
00:45:37,864 --> 00:45:42,327
- But I'm sure I locked it.
- The person on duty said he locked it.

614
00:45:42,327 --> 00:45:45,163
If you're sick, go to the nurse's office.
Why would you rest in here?

615
00:45:45,163 --> 00:45:46,248
Exactly.

616
00:45:46,248 --> 00:45:49,167
Wait, didn't you tell the P.E. teacher
you were going to the nurse's office?

617
00:45:49,167 --> 00:45:53,672
Cut the crap and answer me directly.
Did you steal it?

618
00:45:53,672 --> 00:45:56,508
What the fuck?
You've got to be kidding me.

619
00:45:56,508 --> 00:45:59,010
Fine. If I let you search me
and you find nothing,

620
00:45:59,010 --> 00:46:00,846
then what are you gonna do?

621
00:46:00,846 --> 00:46:03,348
If you find nothing!

622
00:46:03,348 --> 00:46:05,316
I swear, I'll make you regret this.

623
00:46:10,313 --> 00:46:12,899
Fine, look.

624
00:46:12,899 --> 00:46:14,909
Look. I said, look.

625
00:46:16,069 --> 00:46:18,280
See anything? Huh? Look!

626
00:46:18,280 --> 00:46:22,416
- See? There's nothing here! Huh?!
- You haven't checked your locker yet.

627
00:46:24,411 --> 00:46:28,749
What, you've even got a padlock on it.
Must be something important in there, huh?

628
00:46:28,749 --> 00:46:31,926
"Important"? There's nothing in there.

629
00:46:32,836 --> 00:46:35,346
I don't want you invading my privacy.

630
00:46:36,173 --> 00:46:38,182
Privacy?

631
00:46:49,478 --> 00:46:52,071
Isn't this my phone? Huh?

632
00:46:53,023 --> 00:46:56,026
You lost it, so I was just
holding onto it for you.

633
00:46:56,026 --> 00:46:59,154
But you never bothered showing up,
so I couldn't give it back.

634
00:46:59,154 --> 00:47:00,913
Then what's this?

635
00:47:02,282 --> 00:47:05,494
- The class president's AirPods and cash?
- No way.

636
00:47:05,494 --> 00:47:06,828
That's seriously creepy.

637
00:47:06,828 --> 00:47:08,546
Unbelievable.

638
00:47:12,751 --> 00:47:15,553
Sim Sung Hee,
you're still going to deny it?

639
00:47:16,963 --> 00:47:18,799
It wasn't me.

640
00:47:18,799 --> 00:47:22,260
I'm telling you, it wasn't me.
I have no reason to steal.

641
00:47:22,260 --> 00:47:24,012
It's not like my family is poor
or anything.

642
00:47:24,012 --> 00:47:26,848
You're a klepto. You used to steal stuff
back in middle school, remember?

643
00:47:26,848 --> 00:47:28,683
Fuck, I wanna punch her.

644
00:47:28,683 --> 00:47:30,852
- Guys, should we call the cops?
- She's crazy.

645
00:47:30,852 --> 00:47:32,486
She's lost her mind.

646
00:47:35,107 --> 00:47:36,691
Don't let them get to you.

647
00:47:36,691 --> 00:47:38,784
This isn't over yet.

648
00:47:39,778 --> 00:47:41,113
It was Baek Ah Jin!

649
00:47:41,113 --> 00:47:44,165
She set this all up, and I fell for it!

650
00:47:46,159 --> 00:47:47,793
Fuck!

651
00:47:50,288 --> 00:47:51,998
Baek Ah Jin...

652
00:47:51,998 --> 00:47:54,376
She's a bigger piece of shit than I am.

653
00:47:54,376 --> 00:47:57,303
You all need to know
what that bitch is really like!

654
00:47:58,171 --> 00:48:01,800
Kim Jae Oh's ledger...
It's actually Baek Ah Jin's.

655
00:48:01,800 --> 00:48:04,886
It was Baek Ah Jin, you fucking idiots!

656
00:48:04,886 --> 00:48:06,805
What the hell are you talking about?

657
00:48:06,805 --> 00:48:08,181
Hey.

658
00:48:08,181 --> 00:48:10,517
That ledger's mine.

659
00:48:10,517 --> 00:48:12,519
Why say it's Baek Ah Jin's?

660
00:48:12,519 --> 00:48:14,479
You got any proof?

661
00:48:14,479 --> 00:48:17,232
I saw the texts on your phone.

662
00:48:17,232 --> 00:48:20,485
The one about a "boss" and "collections,"
with all the kids' names?

663
00:48:20,485 --> 00:48:23,113
Do you think I'm close enough with her
to be texting back and forth?

664
00:48:23,113 --> 00:48:25,873
Fuck, I'm telling you I saw it.

665
00:48:27,784 --> 00:48:29,418
Look.

666
00:48:31,788 --> 00:48:33,756
Where is this so-called text?

667
00:48:36,209 --> 00:48:38,177
Well?

668
00:48:38,712 --> 00:48:42,340
If you're not lying, they should be
on this phone, right?

669
00:48:42,340 --> 00:48:46,928
This is the first I've touched my phone
since you stole it.

670
00:48:46,928 --> 00:48:51,433
Shit. Now that I think about it,
I'm fucking pissed.

671
00:48:51,433 --> 00:48:55,611
It wasn't enough to steal my phone?
You had to go through my texts, too?

672
00:48:57,856 --> 00:49:00,609
That Baek Ah Jin?
She's seeing the art teacher.

673
00:49:00,609 --> 00:49:03,153
I saw them. I swear I saw them!

674
00:49:03,153 --> 00:49:04,912
Holding hands.

675
00:49:05,447 --> 00:49:09,159
They were talking about "true love."
It was really something else.

676
00:49:09,159 --> 00:49:10,918
Sim Sung Hee!

677
00:49:12,954 --> 00:49:15,957
- Hey, hey!
- You think you can say whatever you want?

678
00:49:15,957 --> 00:49:17,167
Is she a psycho or something?

679
00:49:17,167 --> 00:49:21,792
Let me tell you a secret, too.
About who our homeroom teacher's marrying.

680
00:49:21,792 --> 00:49:22,839
The art teacher.

681
00:49:22,839 --> 00:49:25,592
How dare you spread ridiculous rumors!

682
00:49:25,592 --> 00:49:27,469
Hey, please calm down.

683
00:49:27,469 --> 00:49:30,938
Hey, Baek Ah Jin, why don't you explain?
What is all this nonsense about?

684
00:49:31,723 --> 00:49:35,185
The art teacher was really worried about me,

685
00:49:35,185 --> 00:49:41,198
so he referred me
to the True Love Counseling Center.

686
00:49:41,942 --> 00:49:44,201
I think that's what she must have seen.

687
00:49:44,861 --> 00:49:48,198
You heard that and now you're going around
saying you saw something,

688
00:49:48,198 --> 00:49:51,451
that they have a thing, making it all up
and causing all this chaos, huh?

689
00:49:51,451 --> 00:49:54,579
And another thing. Did you steal all this?
Answer me!

690
00:49:54,579 --> 00:49:56,540
No, I didn't! I told you I didn't!

691
00:49:56,540 --> 00:50:01,795
You were the only one in class during gym.
If you didn't steal, why were you here?

692
00:50:01,795 --> 00:50:04,597
Didn't you tell the teacher you were going
to the nurse's office?

693
00:50:08,427 --> 00:50:10,228
That's because...

694
00:50:12,055 --> 00:50:14,474
I was supposed to meet Joon Seo.

695
00:50:14,474 --> 00:50:18,486
Yoon Joon Seo, is that true?

696
00:50:19,312 --> 00:50:23,400
I was in the equipment room the whole time
cleaning with the gym captain.

697
00:50:23,400 --> 00:50:25,152
Yeah, that's right.

698
00:50:25,152 --> 00:50:29,872
- How could you do this to me?
- Seriously, how far will she take this?

699
00:50:31,700 --> 00:50:34,919
How could you do this to me? Joon Seo, how?

700
00:50:35,996 --> 00:50:38,039
I warned you, didn't I?

701
00:50:38,039 --> 00:50:40,383
I told you not to mess with Baek Ah Jin.

702
00:50:47,215 --> 00:50:50,685
Sim Sung Hee, that's enough.
You're coming with me.

703
00:50:51,803 --> 00:50:53,521
Come with me now!

704
00:50:54,514 --> 00:50:56,691
I'm not going! Damn it!

705
00:50:58,769 --> 00:51:00,570
Dude, this is legendary.

706
00:51:01,980 --> 00:51:03,948
Hey, post this online.

707
00:51:08,403 --> 00:51:11,372
- Wow, this is insane.
- Totally insane.

708
00:51:12,741 --> 00:51:15,952
The class president's AirPods and cash?

709
00:51:15,952 --> 00:51:19,581
I'm telling you, it wasn't me.
I have no reason to steal.

710
00:51:19,581 --> 00:51:21,291
It's not like my family is poor
or anything.

711
00:51:21,291 --> 00:51:25,011
You're a klepto. You used to steal stuff
back in middle school, remember?

712
00:51:31,051 --> 00:51:34,846
[Exposing The Truth About Sim Sung Hee,
Daughter Of Lawyer Sim Geun Seop]

713
00:51:34,846 --> 00:51:37,766
[Unlike In Middle School,
Her School Life Was Relatively...]

714
00:51:37,766 --> 00:51:40,644
[With Attorney Sim Geun Seop]

715
00:51:40,644 --> 00:51:46,574
[Worry about your own family first.
The Truth About Sim Geun Seop's Daughter.]

716
00:51:57,119 --> 00:51:59,621
[Submit]
[I Will Hold Your Hand: Legal Counsel]

717
00:51:59,621 --> 00:52:02,632
[Viewer Comments: Worry About Your Family First]

718
00:52:05,085 --> 00:52:07,254
[Look At Your Family Before You Judge.
Teach Your Daughter Some Decency.]

719
00:52:07,254 --> 00:52:09,506
[He's Still Practicing Law After This?
No Shame.]

720
00:52:09,506 --> 00:52:12,342
She's not my daughter!
How could you do this to me?

721
00:52:12,342 --> 00:52:16,596
- Did you have fun with that whore?
- Fun? Show some class, will you?

722
00:52:16,596 --> 00:52:21,234
Class? Try keeping it in your pants!
I asked if you slept with her!

723
00:52:34,114 --> 00:52:37,750
- Leaving early?
- What do you want? Get lost.

724
00:52:38,326 --> 00:52:40,662
See? I told you.

725
00:52:40,662 --> 00:52:44,507
In movies, it's the clueless ones like you
who always die first.

726
00:52:45,500 --> 00:52:48,754
Shut the fuck up!
This is all because of...

727
00:52:48,754 --> 00:52:51,506
Don't you dare say this is my fault.

728
00:52:51,506 --> 00:52:53,216
This is on you.

729
00:52:53,216 --> 00:52:56,511
You're the one who went through my things,
poured water all over me,

730
00:52:56,511 --> 00:52:59,480
and even trashed my lunch tray.

731
00:53:00,932 --> 00:53:01,975
And I just let it happen.

732
00:53:01,975 --> 00:53:06,229
You think I don't know
you're the one who framed me?

733
00:53:06,229 --> 00:53:10,859
If you were a little less stupid,
things might have turned out differently.

734
00:53:10,859 --> 00:53:12,152
What?

735
00:53:12,152 --> 00:53:17,540
Do you really think that was
Joon Seo's handwriting on the board?

736
00:53:18,366 --> 00:53:20,911
But at this point,
who really cares who wrote it?

737
00:53:20,911 --> 00:53:25,582
What matters is that now,
no one will listen to a word you say.

738
00:53:25,582 --> 00:53:28,301
No one will believe you.

739
00:53:30,045 --> 00:53:34,007
And no one even likes you.

740
00:53:34,007 --> 00:53:36,635
You're a fucking psycho.

741
00:53:36,635 --> 00:53:39,596
You really never suspected Joon Seo?
Not even once?

742
00:53:39,596 --> 00:53:43,190
You really thought he actually liked you?

743
00:53:44,017 --> 00:53:47,069
As if, Sung Hee.

744
00:53:48,271 --> 00:53:52,609
You should've known when to stop.

745
00:53:52,609 --> 00:53:55,946
Fight me all you want.
You're the only one who'll lose.

746
00:53:55,946 --> 00:53:58,706
I've got powerful people backing me up.

747
00:53:59,783 --> 00:54:01,542
You don't.

748
00:54:02,285 --> 00:54:05,455
Because you're an orphan. You bitch.

749
00:54:05,455 --> 00:54:08,333
- You think I'm just going to let this go?
- Sung Hee.

750
00:54:08,333 --> 00:54:12,720
I wonder who Teacher Kwak
was having an affair with.

751
00:54:16,216 --> 00:54:20,762
Ugh, now that Teacher Kwak got fired,
all that money we spent was a total waste.

752
00:54:20,762 --> 00:54:22,973
Who on earth did she get caught
having an affair with?

753
00:54:22,973 --> 00:54:25,851
She said she needed legal advice,
so your dad even helped her out.

754
00:54:25,851 --> 00:54:28,569
Did you like my gift?

755
00:54:34,734 --> 00:54:36,994
If your dad gets branded as the
"Infidelity Lawyer,"

756
00:54:38,738 --> 00:54:41,199
his own firm won't even protect him.

757
00:54:41,199 --> 00:54:43,785
Then your father's reputation will be ruined,

758
00:54:43,785 --> 00:54:46,997
and you'll be known as the thieving
daughter of the infidelity lawyer.

759
00:54:46,997 --> 00:54:51,717
Do you think your parents
will still have your back then?

760
00:54:52,586 --> 00:54:56,222
How will you fare,
having to live with that label?

761
00:54:56,798 --> 00:55:01,686
You really deluded yourself
into thinking you could beat me.

762
00:55:03,972 --> 00:55:06,148
That was never going to happen, Sung Hee.

763
00:55:08,518 --> 00:55:12,947
Like you said, I'm pretty much an orphan.

764
00:55:14,107 --> 00:55:17,034
But it's not like I never had parents
to begin with.

765
00:55:35,712 --> 00:55:37,346
Help me.

766
00:55:39,674 --> 00:55:43,603
I just got rid of them.
They were my first X.

767
00:55:44,596 --> 00:55:48,975
[Lim Sun Ye: Her First X]

768
00:55:55,065 --> 00:55:56,908
Sung Hee.

769
00:55:58,944 --> 00:56:02,079
It was fun having you as my target.

770
00:56:06,493 --> 00:56:08,336
Thanks.

771
00:56:09,121 --> 00:56:12,048
For making school less boring.

772
00:56:26,054 --> 00:56:29,690
What do I think of Baek Ah Jin, you ask?

773
00:56:31,183 --> 00:56:34,486
She's always been a great actress, even as a kid.

774
00:56:35,313 --> 00:56:38,366
She always wore whatever mask
the situation called for.

775
00:56:40,527 --> 00:56:43,120
She's a demon.

776
00:56:43,697 --> 00:56:48,125
A demon in human skin.
